==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Financier
<hw>Fin`an*cier"</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>financier</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One charged with the
administration of finance; an officer who administers the public
revenue; a treasurer.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One skilled in financial operations; one acquainted
with money matters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Financier</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Financier
<hw>Fin`an*cier"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Financiered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Financiering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To conduct financial
operations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Finary</ent>⟦br⟧
